Get to your working dir and clone the github repo:
$ git clone https://github.com/simonspa/cmspxltb-analysis.git .

Get the build_env.sh from here:
$ cp /afs/cern.ch/work/s/simonspa/public/eutelescope.git .
and modify the $MYPATH variable to match your actual installation path

Create the build directory:
$ mkdir build && cd build
Source some stuff for cmake execution:
$ source /afs/cern.ch/work/x/xshi/public/ILCSOFT/v01-17-03/init_ilcsoft.sh
$ source
/afs/cern.ch/work/x/xshi/public/ILCSOFT/v01-17-03/ILCSoft.cmake.env.sh
Run Cmake and compile:
$ cmake ..
$ make install -j
$ cd ..

Source your personal environment:
$ source build_env.sh
...and run.
